                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/222: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-02-20T10:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 20, 1922—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 22—3:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>55. My number 43, February 10, 11 a.m. Representative of Ministry of
                    Communications reports that information received by Ministry from Moss<note
                        n="15" xml:id="d645fn15">Barnes Moss, representative in China of the Federal
                        Telegraph Company.</note> indicates arrangements made by Federal Company to
                        <pb facs="0968" n="848" xml:id="pg_848"/> secure loan from bankers of two
                    and one-half million gold. Ministry urges that construction of Shanghai station
                    be carried out first as this sum is ample for this purpose and that beginning of
                    work operation hastened as Japanese wireless station near [Peking?] nearly
                    completed and will be operating in April.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
